<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-16T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-16T21:00:00-05:00" n="834" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d834">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2709</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SW2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Spencer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-17T11:00:00+09:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 18, 6.03
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Foreign Office confirms their public announcement made yesterday to
                                the effect that Japan recognizes Czecho-Slovak as Allied army under
                                Czecho-Slovak National Council.<note n="2" xml:id="d834fn2">The date
                                    of the recognition was Sept. 9.</note>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Reuter</persName> given full text.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SW2">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Spencer</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>